===Noun===
{{en-noun|~}}

# The [[status]] or [[condition]] of something
#: ''The used bookshop wouldn't offer much due to the poor '''shape''' of the book.''
# [[condition|Condition]] of personal [[health]], especially muscular health.
#: ''The vet checked to see what kind of '''shape''' the animal was in.''
#: ''We exercise to keep in good physical '''shape'''.''
# The [[appearance]] of something in terms of its arrangement in space, especially its [[outline]]; often a basic [[geometric]] [[two-dimensional]] [[figure]].
#: ''He cut a square '''shape''' out of the cake.''
#: ''What '''shape''' shall we use for the cookies? Stars, circles, or diamonds?''
# [[form|Form]]; [[formation]].
#* '''2006''', Berdj Kenadjian, Martin Zakarian, ''From Darkness to Light'':
#*: What if God's plans and actions do mold the '''shape''' of human events?
# {{lb|en|iron manufacture}} A rolled or hammered piece, such as a bar, beam, angle iron, etc., having a cross section different from merchant bar.
# {{lb|en|iron manufacture}} A piece which has been roughly forged nearly to the form it will receive when completely forged or fitted.
# {{lb|en|cookery|now|rare}} A [[mould#Noun|mould]] for making [[blancmange]], [[jelly]], etc., or a piece of such food formed moulded into a particular shape.
#* {{RQ:West Return of the Soldier|page=92|passage=And if I&nbsp;'m late for supper there&nbsp;'s a dish of macaroni cheese you must put in the oven and a tin of tomatoes to eat with it. And there is a little rhubarb and '''shape'''.}}
#* '''1978''', {{w|Jane Gardam}}, ''God on the Rocks'', Abacus 2014, p. 111:
#*: It was brawn and '''shape''' for high tea.
# {{lb|en|gambling}} A [[loaded]] [[die]].
#* '''1961''', United States. Congress. Senate. Committee on Government Operations. Permanent Subcommittee on Investigations, ''Gambling and Organized Crime: Hearings'' (page 76)
#*: A top cheater seldom ever uses '''shapes''' or loaded dice because they do not assure you of winning.
# {{lb|en|programming}} In the [[Hack]] [[programming language]], a group of [[data]] [[field]]s each of which has a [[name]] and a [[data type]].

